Border collie Don nudged the controls of a tractor on to the M74 near Abington in South Lanarkshire . 
  Owner Tom Hamilton was tending to a lamb when he took control of the vehicle . 
  The tractor smashed through a fence and crashed into the central reservation . 
  Don was unhurt but the incident caused major tailbacks on the motorway . 
  Traffic Scotland tweeted that a dog had 'taken control of tractor'